# Keep `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` Up To Date

`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` is the canonical architecture reference. Whenever a change
alters the architecture, update the relevant section(s) of that file **in the same
change** (do not defer it).

## Update the doc when you change any of:

- **Database** (§4 + ER diagram): new/removed/renamed tables, columns, enums,
  indexes, constraints, relationships, or Alembic migrations.
- **Backend** (§3, §8): new/removed services, repositories, routers, or endpoints;
  changed request/response schemas, dependencies, or middleware.
- **RAG pipeline** (§5): any change to parse/OCR/clean/chunk/embed/index/retrieve/
  rerank/generate stages or the models used.
- **LangGraph / agents** (§6, §7): new/removed nodes, graphs, agents, tools, or
  wiring; a placeholder becoming real (update ⚠/✗ flags).
- **Frontend** (§9): new/removed routes, pages, hooks, or service functions; mock
  data becoming real.
- **Infrastructure** (§1): new Docker Compose services or data-flow changes.
- **Limitations / Roadmap** (§13, §14): keep ✓ / ⚠ / ✗ status accurate.

## How to update

- Edit only the affected section(s); keep Mermaid diagrams consistent with the text.
- Preserve the ✓ (done) / ⚠ (partial) / ✗ (not implemented / unused) conventions.
- Update the `_Last verified:_` date near the top of the file.
- If you are unsure whether something is wired in vs. defined-but-unused, verify in
  the code before writing.
